        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer89542477" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14659314578394946640">This book seems like a precursor to Zora Neale Hurston&apos;s works - it has the dialect of an isolated black community in South Carolina, and a very strong female character in Sister Mary - in all her strengths and weaknesses. I really cared about all the characters - plus the descriptions of the land and the seasons were beautiful.</span>
